  "description": "This dataset comprises simultaneous EEG-fMRI and diffusion-weighted imaging data collected from 28 healthy adults (16 female; age range 19-42 years, mean age 27.34±6.58 years; 23 right-handed) performing a sustained attention task (gradCPT) along with resting state, checkerboard, and imagery tasks. The multimodal neuroimaging acquisition combines 64-channel EEG recordings with 3T MRI data to investigate neural correlates of sustained attention. Both raw and preprocessed data are provided, enabling comprehensive analysis of brain activity across multiple imaging modalities.",
  "methods_description": "Data were acquired from 28 healthy adults (16 female; age range 19-42 years, mean age 27.34±6.58 years) using simultaneous EEG-fMRI recording. fMRI and DWI data were collected on a 3T Siemens Magnetom Prisma scanner, while EEG was recorded using 64 channels (Brain Product BrainCap MR with Multirodes). Participants performed multiple tasks including resting state (eyes open and closed), checkerboard stimulation (15Hz), gradCPT sustained attention task, and imagery task. Structural MRI images were defaced to ensure participant anonymity.",
